The paper deals with distributed algorithms and network protocols, which are typically studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also involves the study of network structures and data structures distributed over the nodes, which falls under the Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of certificates and proofs in the distributed algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also involves information theory and communication complexity, which are studied in the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
